      \field{labeltitlesource}{title}
      \field{abstract}{This research paper, "Assessing Gender Bias in Machine Translation -- A Case Study with Google Translate", investigates the presence of gender bias within automated translation tools. The authors explore this by inputting gender-neutral sentences, specifically job titles and adjectives, in various languages into Google Translate and observing the gendered pronouns in the English output. Their findings reveal a strong tendency for Google Translate to default to male pronouns, particularly for professions stereotypically associated with men, and they demonstrate that this bias does not simply reflect real-world gender distributions in the workplace. Ultimately, the study highlights how machine learning systems can inadvertently perpetuate societal biases and calls for the development of debiasing techniques to ensure greater fairness in such technologies.}
